-- Schneider Seeks Faster Growth in Germany, Financial Times Deutschland Says
-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 2010-10-18T05:17:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/schneider-seeks-faster-growth-in-germany-financial-times-deutschland-says.html
Schneider Electric SA , the world’s
biggest maker of circuit breakers, is targeting accelerated
sales growth in Germany next year with energy-saving technology,
the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing an interview
with Rada Rodriguez, who heads the company’s German business.  Sales in Germany are on course to rise more than 10
percent, to about 1 billion euros ($1.4 billion), this year and
to increase still faster next year, according to the newspaper.
Schneider aims to capture customers from Siemens AG and ABB
Ltd., Rodriguez told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Holger Elfes  in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at 
 cperri@bloomberg.net . 